latestPosts.caption:
This is the part no one claps for.
The breaks.
The burn.
The battle in the head.

#hyroxindia

19.07.25

HYROX DELHI ‘25

We did it!

From a non runner to a racer.
From giving up early to a finisher.

This may not have been my best. I still had gas in the tank and ik i could’ve saved more time.
But, honestly this journey was never just about the race.
The main event was the prep;
When no one was watching, and i still chose to show up. I remember how i felt at the start of this journey; self doubt, frustrations, second guessing, painful days. 
Wondering if i even belonged here?
The prep broke me down before it built me up.
And the finish line? That was just a beginning. 

Here’s to showing up, falling short, growing stronger and doing hard things anyway.

#firsthyrox ✅

6 weeks of @hyrox prep.
My first ever race.
And i’m damn proud i finished it.

I trained hard and went in aiming for a sub-90mins finish.
But, this race had other plans.

• my specs broke mid race, lost vision halfway.
• i underestimated sled pull completely. Rope was elastic like. Tried every technique i knew.
• took break only after walking lunges. My legs were gone.
• calf cramps during the final run slowed me down. And the wall balls which i thought were my strongest point; absolutely crushed me.
• my 1k row usually takes 3:30-4:00mins, here it took me 7.

But here is the biggest shock, i spent 24mins in the Roxzone.
I thought walking through it would help me conserve energy.
But each loop was around 200m long.
Across station and transition, i was walking almost 1.5km and bleeding time without realising it.

Hyrox tested everything; my training, my mind and my ego.
But it gave me a new level of respect for this format.

This wasn’t the race i imagined, but it was the one i needed.
And trust me, this is just the beginning. 

#hyroxdelhi #hyroxindia #firstrace #hyroxtraining

latestPosts.caption:
Everyone’s posting their 4s and 5s.
So, here i am dropping my 7 like it’s hot😌

#rainyrun #strava #hybrid

Training, eating, recovering, repeating.🫠

1. Died doing metcon.
2. Survived on protein shakes for weeks, so i made dumplings to feel something.
3. Wore Goku in the hope of beating him one day.
4. Ice bathed like im preparing for war.
5. RHR at 57 but brain at 100
6. Wrapped my pink straps around the bar like my life depends on it.
7. OG glycogen bowl
8. Recovery is now a full time job.
9. Progress selfie for moral support.
10. Running prep.
11. Turkish get ups, dramatic but effective.
12. Ice my traps bc one upper body day turned me into a bodybuilder.
13. Cheese toast🫣 call it maintenance please.
14. Proof i exist outside the gym.

#hybridlife

latestPosts.caption:
I missed the last race.
I was injured.
I overthought it.
And then I watched it happen without me.

So this time, I signed up before my doubts got a second chance.

And even while preparing,
I planned to give up again.
Too sore, too slow, too far behind.
But something in me said, “not this time”.

Maybe I won’t be the fastest.
But I’ll be on that floor.
And that’s already a win I wasn’t sure I’d fight for.

#hyroxindia #justdoit
